          "411 students",
          "19 courses ",
          "LMS logs",
          "None Specified",
          "[MC_ORIENT, CONTENT_ACCESS, MC_EVAL, MCQ:IN, MCQ_CO]",
          "Authors extract logs and assign them to different event categories. These categories are subsequently mapped into SRL constructs (Planning, Work on Task, Evaluation). \n\nThe authors perform Trajectory Mining to form clusters on the data from the 19 courses.",
          "Life Trajectory Miner, followed by First-Order Markov Models",
          "-",
          "3",
          "Cluster 1: No clear dominating strategy but these students seem to start with knowledge-buiding activities.\n\nCluster 2: Regular transitions between formative assessments and knowledge building activities\n\nCluster 3: More regular planning and reflection relative to other works. Regular transitions between setting goals and making plans have been registered. ",
          "Temporal modelling seems to be somewaht limited in large-scale endeavours, especially ones considering different course structures and contextual conditions. \n\n\nTemporal modelling of SRL constructs may reqauire refinments.\n",
          "Authors use a Course-Agnostic approach to ideintify regular transitions in behvaior from students across diffferent courses.\n\nIn total, the authors identify 3 main clusters.\n\nThis is followed by a subsequent regression analysis that tries to “explain group membership vs grade. Best students were the ones in Cluster 3. ",
          "Lack of descriptive features.\n\nExtraction of general patterns from a very diverse subset of courses. \n\n\n\n"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 6
    }
  ],
