    {
      "id": "a03a5030-a467-491d-ae50-e8d384e9dfe6",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The abstract starts by criticizing the fact that the showcase of new models in LA is to show how well they perform in a single course. The authors attempt to replicate a temporal model of SRL taxonomies with the caveat of generalizing it to 411 students in 19 courses. Techniques used combine hierarchical clustering with Hidden Markov Models.",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "a03a5030-a467-491d-ae50-e8d384e9dfe6",
        "parent": {
